{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id9069fcfd-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4086"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4086"},"text":"§ 4086.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Entitlement to vote in a State in a Federal election; preconditions; applicability","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id9069fcfe-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4086/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Except as provided in subsection (b) and in such manner as shall be otherwise authorized by a State or other jurisdiction within the territory of the United States, a member of the Service residing outside the United States shall, in addition to any entitlement to vote in a State in a Federal election under section 3 of the Overseas Citizens Voting Rights Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1973dd–1"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 1973dd–1","children":[],"tail":"), be entitled to vote in a Federal election in the State in which such member was last domiciled immediately before entering the Service if such member—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id9069fcff-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4086/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" makes an election of that State;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id9069fd00-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4086/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" notifies that State of such election and notifies any other States in which he or she is entitled to vote of such election; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id9069fd01-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4086/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" otherwise meets the requirements of such Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1973dd"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 1973dd","children":[],"tail":" et seq.]."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id9069fd02-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s4086/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The provisions of subsection (a) shall apply only to an individual who becomes a member of the Service on or after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-11-22"},"text":"November 22, 1983","children":[],"tail":", and shall not apply to an individual who registers to vote in a State in which he is entitled to vote under section 3 of Overseas Citizens Voting Rights Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1973dd–1"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 1973dd–1","children":[],"tail":"]."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id9069fd03-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/465/tI/s906"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–465, title I, § 906","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/164/tI/s129/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–164, title I, § 129(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-11-22"},"text":"Nov. 22, 1983","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/97/1027"},"text":"97 Stat. 1027","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id9069fd04-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id9069fd05-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id9069fd06-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Overseas Citizens Voting Rights Act, referred to in text, probably means the Overseas Citizens Voting Rights Act of 1975, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/203"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–203","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-01-02"},"text":"Jan. 2, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/89/1142"},"text":"89 Stat. 1142","children":[],"tail":", which was classified generally to subchapter I–E (§ 1973dd et seq.) of chapter 20 of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare, and which was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/410/tII/s203"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–410, title II, § 203","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-08-28"},"text":"Aug. 28, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/930"},"text":"100 Stat. 930","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
